{
  "text": "Compared to intermittent dosing, continuous infusion of vancomycin could result in the following outcomes: (1) [CITATION_1] Hanrahan et al [CITATION_2] conducted a meta-analysis of seven studies of vancomycin administration by continuous vs intermittent infusion and identified a non-significant trend of reduced nephrotoxicity in those who received vancomycin by continuous infusion (risk ratio=0.799, P=0.299). However, a newer meta-analysis of eleven studies by Hao et al [CITATION_3] revealed that patients treated with continuous infusion of vancomycin had a significantly lower incidence of nephrotoxicity compared with patients receiving intermittent infusion (relative risk=0.61, P<0.001), whereas the clinical efficacy was not significantly different.",
  "correct_citation": {
